    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You quickly flash your blade at a 45 degree angle with a burst of icy chakra, stopping their movement dead in their tracks.</em><br />  As part of the activation of this jutsu, you must be airborne, falling, or be targeting an airborne or falling creature. Make a melee taijutsu attack targeting a creature in range. On a hit, the creature takes your weapon's damage + 1d6 Cold damage, sending them crashing down, knocking them <em><strong>Prone</strong></em>, and <em><strong>Stunning</strong></em> them until the end of the current round, and returning to a space within 5 feet, taking no fall damage upon landing.</p><p><em><strong>EX Skill.</strong></em> When you would cast this jutsu, you may also spend <strong>1 </strong><em><strong>Heat Point</strong></em> to lower it's casting time to 1 Bonus Action and replacing the <em><strong>Chain 3</strong></em> keyword with <em><strong>Chain X</strong></em>. When this jutsu is granted the <em><strong>Chain X</strong></em> keyword it gains the following effects:<br />  If this jutsu is cast as a <em><strong>Chain 1</strong></em>, instead of being <em><strong>Stunned</strong></em>, the target creature must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save they gain 1 rank of <em><strong>Chilled</strong></em>.<br />  If this jutsu is cast as a <em><strong>Chain 2</strong></em>, instead of being <em><strong>Stunned</strong></em>, the target creature gains a -2 penalty to their AC while <em><strong>Prone</strong></em>.</p><p><strong>At Higher Ranks:</strong> For each rank you cast this jutsu above C-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3, and the Cold damage dealt by 1d6.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
